Cell["\<\
Create an interactive plot that allows us to move the direction vector around \
360 degrees, and show how it determines a single variable calculus curve, and \
show that the tangent follows the direction as well. This is interactive, we \
can move the base point (a,b) as well as the direction of the unit vector we \
are looking at. The unit vector is displayed in the xy-plane below the \
surface, hence we also include an opacity configuration to be able to see \
through the surface:\
\>", "Section",
